  "diary": "Woke up to perfect weather and decided to make the most of it. Jasper and I started with our usual morning routine—coffee, a neighborhood loop, then I drove out to Green Lake for a proper walk. The water was packed with boats and paddleboarders taking advantage of the 72-degree sunshine. I spent a good hour just watching people, letting my mind wander. Work stress melts away on days like this. Met up with my friend at Molly Moon's for coffee and a walk—nothing fancy, just what we needed. Back home, I spun some vinyl I'd picked up last week, organized the collection a bit. Made a simple dinner, gave Jasper all the attention he could handle. The evening was quiet, just me, the records, and a book. These Sundays remind me why I love this city.",
  "thought_process": "I chose to prioritize downtime today because my job demands constant focus and quick decisions—being an air traffic controller means I need these slow Sundays to decompress. The beautiful weather was irresistible, so I built the day around outdoor moments rather than staying cooped up. Meeting my friend felt important too; I realized mid-afternoon that I needed human connection beyond just Jasper. The vinyl organizing scratched an itch I've had all week—something tactile and creative. I kept dinner simple because after such a leisurely day, I didn't want to break the mood with complicated cooking. The calm world events today meant I could actually relax without half-listening to news in the background.",
